The paper discusses the use of evolutionary algorithms to generate progress in the co-evolution of predator and prey robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The focus is on the behavior of the evolving robots, which suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed algorithm involves filtering out opportunistic variations, which could be related to neural networks and optimization (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the accumulation of progress over many generations, which could be related to systems and control (cs.SY).
